  "body": "Bug: Use getDerivedStateFromProps cause this.props not update in render and componentDidUpdate\r\n\r\n**What is the current behavior?**\r\n\r\n// 1: use static getDerivedStateFromProps, this.props won't update in render and componentDidUpdate\r\n\r\n// 2: use componentWillReceiveProps, this.props can update in render and componentDidUpdate\r\n\r\n**What is the expected behavior?**\r\n\r\nuse static getDerivedStateFromProps, this.props also can update in render and componentDidUpdate\r\n\r\n**Which versions of React, and which browser / OS are affected by this issue? Did this work in previous versions of React?**\r\n\r\n\"react\": \"^16.4.0\" and \"react\": \"^16.3.1\"\r\nChrome v67.0.3396.87\r\n",
